'most reliable weather records' refers to the records with the highest combined reliability and quality scores; 
 'reliability' refers to the data_reliability column, representing the reliability score of the data (0-100); 
 'quality score' refers to the quality_score column, representing the quality score of the data (0-100).

; The past month refers to the last 30 days from the current date; 
; The current weather condition refers to the most recent weather data entry for each location;
; Average data quality score represents the average quality score of the most recent data validation for each location.
